        "action": "Applications for ILR - Standard service failure should be illegal ",
        "additional_details": "The law should be changed so the Home Office can face legal sanctions if they fail to meet their standard service targets.\r\n \r\nhttps://www.google.co.uk/amp/s/www.bbc.co.uk/news/amp/uk-england-41096675\r\n \r\nhttps://www.ein.org.uk/news/independent-increasing-home-office-delays-deciding-settlement-visas-despite-falling",
        "background": "Families are facing emotional distress from Home Office delays to process applications with some taking up to 2 years when their standard service is up to 6 months. During this time applicants are restricted on what to do since the passports are kept by HO and there\u2019s no resident residence status.",
